{
  "texts": [
    "Biomedical healthcare on vision language modelsThis section elaborates on the training of vision language models for biomedical imaging, and their practical applications in the biomedical healthcare sector.",
    "How to train vision language models for biomedical imagingDeep neural networks demonstrate outstanding performance in various vision tasks, including image classification, object detection, and instance segmentation.",
    "A key to this success in the foundation model era is the concept of pre-training, which, unlike in NLP where it usually involves language models, traditionally meant training on extensive labeled image datasets like ImageNet [48].",
    "More recently, diverse learning methods have been introduced to overcome limitations of conventional supervised learning, such as generalization errors and spurious correlations.",
    "We examine several methodologies suitable for imaging applications as follows:• Unsupervised Pre-training: Unsupervised pre-training leverages large volumes of unlabeled image data to learn rich feature representations without the guidance of explicit annotations."
  ]
}